member.value:
true if the application is the default 
for its class;
otherwise, false.

true if only top-level product types should be included; 
 false if top-level product types should not be included; 
 null otherwise.

true if cards are updated using remaining hours;
otherwise, false, indicating that cards are updated
using percent complete.

true if the field on the API object should
be cleared when no value has been provided;
otherwise, false.

If true, will filter on the tickets being in a
 status class of "New", "In Process", or "On Hold";
 otherwise, will apply no extra filtering.

If not loaded, will be null.
When loaded, will be true if the "Respond By" component of the ticket's SLA has been violated; 
otherwise, false.

If not loaded, will be null.
When loaded, will be true if the "Resolve By" component of the ticket's SLA has been violated; 
otherwise, false.

true if the action was responsible for completing the step;
otherwise, false if the step remained active after the action
or null for legacy steps for whom this information is not available.
